Step 1: Create a Spring Boot Project in IntelliJ IDEA

Open IntelliJ IDEA â†’ Click on New Project.
Select Spring Initializr.
Choose Maven or Gradle as the project type.
Select Spring Boot Version (e.g., 3.0.0).
Add dependencies:
Spring Web (for REST API)
Spring Data JPA (for database interactions)
H2 Database (in-memory database)
Click Finish to create the project.
-------
Step 2: Configure application.properties
Create a file in src/main/resources/application.properties to configure the H2 database.
--------
Step 3: Create the Model (Entity)
Create a class named Product.java inside the package com.example.crud.model.
------------
Step 4: Create a Repository
Create an interface named ProductRepository.java inside com.example.crud.repository.

Explanation:
JpaRepository<Product, Long> â†’ Provides built-in CRUD operations for Product with Long as the ID type.
---------
Step 5: Create the Service Layer
Create a class named ProductService.java inside com.example.crud.service.

Explanation:
@Service â†’ Marks the class as a service component.
@Autowired â†’ Injects the repository dependency.
CRUD Methods:
saveProduct() â†’ Saves a new product or updates an existing one.
getAllProducts() â†’ Fetches all products from the database.
getProductById() â†’ Retrieves a product by ID.
deleteProduct() â†’ Deletes a product by ID.
--------------------------------------------
Step 6: Create a Controller
Create a class named ProductController.java inside com.example.crud.controller.

Explanation:
@RestController â†’ Defines a REST API controller.
@RequestMapping("/products") â†’ Base path for API endpoints.
@PostMapping â†’ Handles POST requests (Create).
@GetMapping â†’ Handles GET requests (Read).
@PutMapping â†’ Handles PUT requests (Update).
@DeleteMapping â†’ Handles DELETE requests (Delete).
@RequestBody
-----------------------------------------
Step 7: Run the Application
Open IntelliJ IDEA.
Go to CrudApplication.java.
Click Run (or use mvn spring-boot:run in the terminal).


