Step 8: Test the Endpoints Using Postman or CURL
Create a Product (POST)

2ï¸âƒ£ Testing the API using Postman or CURL
You can test the CRUD operations by sending HTTP requests.

ðŸ”¹ Open API Endpoints in a Browser/Postman
Since this is a REST API, you wonâ€™t see a UI, but you can test it using Postman, cURL, or directly in the browser.

ðŸ”¹ Test API Endpoints
âœ… Create a Product (POST)
Using Postman:

1.Open Postman.
2.Select POST and enter the URL:

bash--> http://localhost:8080/products

3.In the Body (JSON format), enter:
json --->
{
  "name": "Laptop",
  "price": 50000
}
4.Click Send. You should receive a response with the created product.

OR
Using cURL (in the terminal):

sh--->
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/products -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name": "Laptop", "price": 50000}'

_________________________
âœ… Get All Products (GET)
Browser: Open
bash-->
http://localhost:8080/products
You should see JSON output like:
json--->
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Laptop",
    "price": 50000
  }
]
OR   Using cURL:
sh-->
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/products

âœ… Get a Product by ID (GET)
URL:
bash-->
http://localhost:8080/products/1
Response:
json-->
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Laptop",
  "price": 50000
}


âœ… Update a Product (PUT)
Using Postman:
1.Use PUT method.
2.URL:
bash-->
http://localhost:8080/products/1

3.Body (JSON):
json-->
{
  "name": "Gaming Laptop",
  "price": 70000
}
4.Click Send.


âœ… Delete a Product (DELETE)
Using Postman:

Set method to DELETE
Use URL:
bash-->
http://localhost:8080/products/1
Click Send.
Using cURL:

sh-->
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/products/1
